title: Ilhan Omar announces the Democrats will ‘oppose all funding’ for immigration enforcement
description: Democratic Representative for Minnesota, Ilhan Omar, has announced the party has officially adopted a position to defund ICE.  Omar states the Democrats will hold ICE accountable and will "oppose all funding" for immigration enforcement.  Omar's comments come following the fatal shooting of 37-year-old Renee Good by an ICE officer in the sanctuary city of Minneapolis, Minnesota.  As Omar and the Democrats look to oppose the Trump administration, the president has vowed to stop making payments to sanctuary cities on February 1.

title: US transgender sports ban challenged in Supreme Court
description: The US Supreme Court has been hearing arguments in two cases, challenging bans on transgender athletes in students’ sports.  The argument between Idaho and West Virginia addresses whether state bans are permitted under federal law.  At the heart of both cases is whether the state bans violate equal protection of the 14th Amendment and Title Nine, which bans discrimination and education on the basis of sex.  The states argue their bans are about creating an even playing field.   Across the country, 27 states have enacted restrictions on transgender students participating in sports.  A ruling from the Supreme Court on the Idaho and West Virginia laws is expected in June.

title: Trump calls Romney a ‘stone-cold loser’ for voting against him
description: US President Donald Trump calls former US senator Mitt Romney a “stone-cold loser” during his speech on the American economy.  “We got some real losers …  I got him elected twice,” Mr Trump said.  “Then he votes against me all the time.”

title: Bill Maher brutally unleashes on ‘woke’ Hollywood in savage takedown of celebrity elite
description: Comedian Bill Maher has unleashed on “woke” Hollywood, blaming it as the reason he’ll never win another Emmy.  Maher, while talking on his Club Random podcast, prior to the Golden Globes, unleashed on “woke” members of Hollywood.  Maher was nominated and subsequently lost to fellow comedian Ricky Gervais at the Golden Globes.  While speaking with Train Dreams star Joel Edgerton, Maher said he had been nominated 33 times for an Emmy and claimed they would “never” give it to him.  Throughout his career, Bill Maher has received a total of 42 nominations and one win, according to the Emmys website.

title: Tim Walz brutally ridiculed over embarrassing gaffe
description: Former Liberal senator Hollie Hughes has brutally ridiculed Minnesota Governor Tim Walz over his awkward remarks about “riding” Republicans.  “I think if you’re a Republican, you’d probably get out of the state,” she said.  “Does he even understand what the reference is?”

title: More than 10 people dead following landfill collapse in the Philippines
description: More than 10 people have died in a landslide in the central Philippines.  It occurred at a landfill in Cebu City last week while more than 100 workers were on site.  Rescue crews have found 12 people injured, but 25 people remain unaccounted for.  Investigations into the cause and a review of the country’s waste management system are underway.

title: Northern Territory government to make pepper spray possession a permanent measure
description: Northern Territory Chief Minister Lia Finocchiaro says the state is set to make the personal use of OC spray a permanent measure.  A 12-month trial saw more than 2,000 people buying the spray.   Police say there have been 33 prohibited buyers who have been identified, and they have seized 46 canisters.   The government is now considering bringing in laws to make the personal use of OC spray a permanent measure.

title: ‘So demeaning to women’: Trump rips transgender athletes after Supreme Court hearing
description: US President Donald Trump criticises transgender athletes playing in female sports, following the Supreme Court hearing, claiming Democrats are trying to sell “transgender for everybody”.  “They [Republicans] have horrible policy, thank god they have horrible policy because they're smart, they're evil,” Mr Trump said.  “Young women were the size of his leg; he wouldn't have had to run. He could have just walked.  “It's so ridiculous, it's so demeaning to women.”

title: Trump to cut drug prices by as much as ‘600 per cent’
description: US President Donald Trump claims he has negotiated with drug companies to cut prices by as much as “400, 500, and even 600 per cent”.  “On that alone, we should win the midterms in a landslide,” Mr Trump said.  “The country that pays the lowest price in the world is the price we're going to pay.  “We got that because of tariffs.”

title: ‘Help is on the way’: Donald Trump’s message to Iranian protesters
description: World leaders are waiting to see if US President Donald Trump is serious about military intervention in Iran.  This comes after he sent a message to protesters in Iran, telling them help is on the way.  There are options available to President Trump, such as economic sanctions and cyberattacks.

title: ‘A lot of concerns’ over Albanese’s hate speech bill
description: Nationals Senate Leader Bridget McKenzie claims Labor’s hate speech legislation creates “a lot of cause for concern”.  “There are a lot of concerns about the legislation as it stands,” Ms McKenzie told Sky News Australia.  “Particularly, the Prime Minister’s decision to put migration law changes, gun law changes, free speech changes into the same bill.”

title: Chris Minns appoints two Coordinators General to assist community after Bondi attack
description: New South Wales Premier Chris Minns announced the appointment of Coordinators General on the one-month anniversary of the Bondi attack.   Mr Minns spoke in Sydney, where he appointed NSW Jewish Board of Deputies Chief Executive Michele Goldman and Multicultural NSW Chief Executive Joseph La Posta as the two Coordinators General to lead the ongoing support, to ensure people are getting the assistance they need.   Mr Minns says the chanting of ‘Globalise the Intifada’ should not be allowed to be said on the streets across the country.

title: Donald Trump keeping his ‘cards close to his chest’ by not revealing next steps for Iran
description: US President Trump claims help is on its way for protesters in Iran, where US-based rights groups now say 2,000 people have been killed.   President Trump has declined to clarify Washington’s next steps.  The White House has suggested for days Trump could be taking military action, making it a possibility.   Accurate numbers relating to the death toll are difficult to come by due to an internet blackout.   Protests began in late December as an expression of anger over the economy, but have since transitioned from being primarily about economic grievances to encompassing broader discontent against the Iranian government.

title: Donald Trump threatens 'strong action' against Iran if it starts hanging protesters
description: President Trump has warned his administration will take "very strong action" against Iran if the regime starts hanging protesters.  Trump spoke to CBS News' Tony Dokoupil about what he plans to do if Iran crosses his "red line.”  "If they want to have protests, that's one thing. When they start killing thousands of people, and now you're telling me about hanging, we'll see how that works out for them. It's not going to work out good," Mr Trump said.  This comes as a young Iranian protester is allegedly set to be executed on Wednesday for taking part in the anti-government demonstrations.  More than 10,000 people have reportedly been arrested for participating in the anti-government protests.

title: Joe Rogan comments on the 'horrific' Minnesota ICE shooting footage
description: Podcaster Joe Rogan has responded to the shooting of American woman Renee Good by an ICE agent.  Rogan sat down with Republican Senator Rand Paul, where the two of them discussed ICE raids and the shooting of Good.  Rogan, during his podcast, had questioned the ICE-involved shooting of Good after seeing “horrific” footage.  The podcaster spoke of the officer, expressing the sympathy he felt for them, but stated he believed Renee Good was “turning” the car away from the officer.  “When people say it’s justifiable because the car hit it, it seemed like she was kind of turning the car away,” Rogan said.
